UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS HB 257/EN
1 AN ACT relating to the education assessment and accountability system.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 158 IS CREATED TO
4 READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 (1) As used in this section:
6 (a) "Locally developed indicators of quality" means measures or indicators
7 created or adopted by a local school district that:
8 1. Are aligned with the academic standards established in Section 2 of
9 this Act;
10 2. Allow all students to demonstrate their ability to apply grade-
11 appropriate, standards-driven knowledge, content, and skills in real-
12 world applications; and
13 3. May include additional locally identified indicators related to priorities
14 established by the local community that serve to complement the
15 requirements in subparagraphs 1. and 2. of this paragraph. These
16 indicators may include student well-being, fiscal responsibility, or
17 school safety; and
18 (b) "Vibrant learning" means an educational experience that is:
19 1. Characterized by student agency and the application of knowledge
20 and skills aligned with the academic standards established in Section 2
21 of this Act;
22 2. Developed in partnership with students' families, local communities,
23 and the local workforce; and
24 3. Demonstrated through personalized projects, outputs, experiences, or
25 other produced results reflecting each individual student's academic
26 and career interests.
27 (2) Each local school district may develop and implement a system of locally
Page 1 of 45
HB025720.100 - 1141 - XXXX 4/1/2026 10:41 PM Engrossed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS HB 257/EN
1 developed indicators of quality in accordance with administrative regulations
2 promulgated by the Kentucky Board of Education. The locally developed
3 indicators of quality shall include:
4 (a) Student participation in vibrant learning experiences; and
5 (b) Locally developed indicators of performance.
6 (3) A local school district utilizing a system of locally developed indicators of quality
7 shall:
8 (a) When an indicator involves student data, include student performance data
9 for all students, disaggregated by individual subgroups, where permissible;
10 and
11 (b) Develop a publicly available, online display that clearly communicates each
12 applicable school and the district's performance on the locally developed
13 indicators of quality, disaggregated by individual subgroups, where
14 permissible.
15 (4) The Kentucky Department of Education:
16 (a) Shall offer technical assistance to local school districts in their development
17 of locally developed indicators of quality; and
18 (b) May offer a one (1) time payment to offset costs incurred by local school
19 districts in the development of locally developed indicators of quality. A
20 financial payment provided under this paragraph shall not exceed fifteen
21 thousand dollars ($15,000) per district.
22 (5) The Kentucky Board of Education may promulgate administrative regulations in
23 accordance with KRS Chapter 13A necessary to administer the provisions of this
24 section.
25 Section 2. KRS 158.6453 (Effective July 1, 2026) is amended to read as
26 follows:
27 (1) As used in this section:
