1 transparent process that allows all Kentuckians an opportunity to
2 participate. The department shall ensure the public's assistance in
3 reviewing and suggesting changes to the standards and alignment
4 adjustments to corresponding state assessments by establishing a
5 website dedicated to collecting comments by the public and educators.
6 An independent third party, which has no prior or current affiliation with
7 a curriculum or assessment resources vendor, shall be selected by the
8 department to collect and transmit the comments to the department for
9 dissemination to the appropriate advisory panel for review and
10 consideration.
11 2. Each advisory panel shall review the standards and assessments for its
12 assigned subject matter and grade level and the suggestions made by the
13 public and educators. After completing its review, each advisory panel
14 shall make recommendations for changes to the standards and alignment
15 adjustments for assessments to the appropriate standards and
16 assessments review committee.
17 3. Each standards and assessments review committee shall review the
18 findings and make recommendations to revise or replace existing
19 standards and to adjust alignment of assessments.
20 4. The recommendations shall be published on the website established in
21 this subsection for the purpose of gathering additional feedback from the
22 public. The commissioner shall subsequently present the
23 recommendations and the public feedback to the Interim Joint
24 Committee on Education.
25 5. The commissioner shall subsequently provide a report to the standards
26 and assessments process review committee summarizing the process
27 conducted under this subsection and the resulting recommendations. The
