HB025720.100 - 1141 - XXXX 4/1/2026 10:41 PM Engrossed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS HB 257/EN
1 and four (4) incentives at local districts throughout their secondary
2 career and technical education. For incentive criteria that is
3 achieved more than once at state-operated area technology centers,
4 the incentive shall be counted for the state-operated area
5 technology center where it was first achieved. For incentive
6 criteria that is achieved more than once at local districts, the
7 incentive shall be counted for the local district where it was first
8 achieved;
9 c. The department shall distribute incentives-based funds for each
10 state-operated area technology center or local district based on the
11 center's or district's proportional share of the combined number of
12 qualifying student incentives achieved by students in grade twelve
13 (12) at a state-operated area technology center or within a local
14 district throughout their secondary career and technical education.
15 The incentives-based funds shall be distributed to the state-
16 operated area technology center or local district in which the
17 incentive was achieved; and
18 d. The department shall distribute the state-operated area technology
19 center fund portion to the respective state-operated area
20 technology centers and the local district fund portion to the
21 respective local districts;
22 (d) There shall be no mid-year adjustment to the allocation of career and technical
23 education supplemental funding for a center or local district; and
24 (e) Notwithstanding the restriction in paragraph (b) of this subsection, a district
25 may submit a waiver request to the Office of Career and Technical Education
26 to use a portion of its allocation of supplemental funds for career and
27 technical education programming for students in grades (5) through eight (8).
